DURBAN - Church leaders will provide their take on political murders in KwaZulu-Natal on Thursday.They will be testifying at the Moerane Commission of Inquiry in Durban.This follows an appearance by Sbu Zikode, president of the shack-dweller movement Abahlali baseMjondolo.READ: Abahlali baseMjondolo to testify at Moerane CommissionZikode spoke about the tension between his organisation and the ANC-led eThekwini municipality.He claimed they were being targeted because Abahlali has exposed corruption, particularly in the allocation of houses.Several members have been killed since 2009 and in two cases, a councillor and a police officer were convicted.The commission s term ends in October.eNCA